===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Various explanations exist:
* {{liushu|p}} – [https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:20230208_Chime_bells_of_Marquis_Yi_of_Zeng.jpg a beam from which bells and chimes hang].<ref name="漢多">[https://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word=%E6%A5%AD 漢語多功能字庫 - 字頭 「業」]</ref>
* {{liushu|p}} – a person lifting said beam.<ref name="字源 ">李学勤，2012《字源》，Tianjin: 天津古籍出版社。p.199</ref>
* {{Han compound|丵|大|t1=chisel|t2=person; big|ls=ic}} – to launch a great attack.<ref name="說文新證">季旭昇，2004《說文新證》，台北：藝文印書館印行，2014年9月第二版。p.169</ref>
Up until the {{w|Warring States}} period, the character was written doubled as {{och-l|*𪴨}} and sometimes as {{och-l|*𫨱}}. The latter is a {{liushu|psc|nocap=y}} using {{och-l|*去}} (the original form of {{och-l|盍}}) as a phonetic component. In {{w|bamboo slips}} the vertical stroke of 丵 extended such that the bottom looks like 木.
<references/>

